# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .env.local.example — point a LOCAL build at the NEW Supabase project
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Purpose: test the fresh Supabase project locally WITHOUT touching the
# committed `.env` (which stays on the OnSpace backend until cutover).
#
# Usage:
#     cp .env.local.example .env.local
#     # then paste your NEW project's values below
#
# Why this is safe:
#   • `.env.local` is git-ignored (see .gitignore: `.env*.local`), so it is
#     never committed or pushed — no risk of leaking keys or cutting over prod.
#   • Expo loads `.env.local` and it OVERRIDES `.env` for local dev runs, so the
#     app talks to the new project only on your machine.
#   • Both values are the public/anon-safe pair (Dashboard → Project Settings →
#     API). Never put the service_role key here or anywhere in the app.
#
# When done testing, delete `.env.local` to fall back to the committed `.env`.
# The real cutover (editing `.env`) is a separate, explicit step — not this file.

EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://<your-new-project-ref>.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<your-new-project-anon-public-key>
